<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[189,1399,974,1143]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
In the CRB area, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[386,591,974,1000]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Cloeotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percivali">
<emphasis box="[386,591,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Cloeotis percivali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the southeastern Congolese provinces of Haut-Lomami and Haut-Katanga. Strangely enough, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobs" box="[624,840,1009,1036]" firstAuthor="Jacobs" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="365 - 366" refId="ref266944" refString="Jacobs D. S. 2013. Cloeotis percivali Percival's trident bat (short-eared trident bat). In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 365 - 366. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013">Jacobs (2013: 365)</bibRefCitation>
only refers to one locality: Shinkolobwe. Its Pan- African distribution reaches from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[695,755,1045,1071]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">DRC</collectingCountry>
over 
<collectingCountry box="[823,912,1045,1071]" name="Zambia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[970,1094,1045,1071]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
to northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1293,1350,1045,1071]" name="South Africa" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">RSA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,314,1080,1106]" name="Swaziland" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Swaziland</collectingCountry>
. All of these records are assigned to 
<emphasis box="[747,914,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">C. p. australis</emphasis>
. The nominate subspecies is restricted to southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[341,417,1117,1143]" name="Kenya" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[623,730,1116,1142]" name="Tanzania" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, where it is known from a few isolated specimens.
</paragraph>
